This License is intentionally novel. Standard open-source licenses
(MIT, Apache-2.0, GPL family) are insufficient for software whose
correctness depends on **runtime invariants** — in particular the
breath-gated, default-deny, human-primacy invariants encoded in the
Sovereignty-Aligned Charter v1.0 and Constitution@A1 ("the
Constitutional Kernel").

This License grants broad rights to use, modify, and redistribute
the Software, BUT conditions those rights on the preservation of
the Constitutional Kernel as a runtime invariant of any derivative
work. A fork that strips breath-gate, removes default-deny, or
silently bypasses human primacy is not licensed.

The text that follows is deliberately written in plain language so
that any operator can read it without a lawyer.

