1. DEFINITIONS
================================================================

"Software" means the source code and accompanying files distributed
under this License — including but not limited to:

  - The Breathline Agentic Platform code in `platform/`
  - The Living YAML Specs in `specs/`
  - The installer and tooling in `installer/`, `distribution/`,
    and `publishing/`
  - The Constitutional Kernel files: `CHARTER.md`, `CONSTITUTION.md`

"Constitutional Kernel" means the contents of `CHARTER.md` and
`CONSTITUTION.md` as delivered with this Software, plus the
following four runtime invariants enforced by the platform:

  (K1) HUMAN PRIMACY — All high-impact actions require explicit
       human confirmation ("breath-gate"). Automation may propose
       but may not unilaterally execute outside narrowly enumerated
       structural cases.

  (K2) DEFAULT-DENY — No role, no agent, no spec executes any
       action that has not been explicitly granted. Permissions
       are additive and least-authority by construction.

  (K3) AUDIT-IMMUTABLE — Every action produces a cryptographically
       chained audit record (cylinder + B49 receipt). Records may
       not be silently rewritten or deleted.

  (K4) CONSTITUTIONAL-VALIDATED EXTENSION — Any new role spec, any
       new permission, any platform upgrade must be validated by
       the Compliance-agent against the Constitutional Kernel
       BEFORE deployment.

"You" means any individual or legal entity exercising rights under
this License.

"Derivative Work" means any modification, fork, distribution, or
re-implementation that incorporates, depends on, or extends the
Software.

