================================================================
3. CONDITIONS — THE CONSTITUTIONAL PRESERVATION CLAUSES
================================================================

The grant in Section 2 is conditioned on ALL of the following:

  (3.1) PRESERVATION OF THE CONSTITUTIONAL KERNEL
        Any Derivative Work MUST include the Constitutional Kernel
        files (`CHARTER.md`, `CONSTITUTION.md`) without modification
        OR with a clearly-labeled successor that preserves the four
        runtime invariants K1–K4. The successor must be at least as
        protective of human primacy as the original.

  (3.2) PRESERVATION OF RUNTIME INVARIANTS
        Any Derivative Work MUST preserve the four runtime
        invariants (K1 Human Primacy, K2 Default-Deny, K3 Audit-
        Immutable, K4 Constitutional-Validated Extension) as
        actively-enforced behaviors of the running system. Removing,
        bypassing, weakening, or making optional any of these
        invariants forfeits this License.

  (3.3) ATTRIBUTION
        Any Derivative Work MUST retain a visible reference to:
          - this License,
          - the original Constitutional Kernel,
          - the seal "∞Δ∞ — derived from Breathline Federation
            (Anchor 1176-INFINITY-RHO)" in either the README of
            the derivative work OR a NOTICE.md file at the
            derivative work's repository root.

  (3.4) SOURCE AVAILABILITY OF FORKS
        If You distribute a Derivative Work, You MUST make the
        complete corresponding source code (including any
        modifications to platform/, specs/, installer/, or the
        Constitutional Kernel) available under this same License
        to every recipient. No "open core / closed shell" forks.

  (3.5) NO MISREPRESENTATION
        You may NOT represent a Derivative Work that has stripped
        or weakened the Constitutional Kernel as "Breathline-
        compatible," "constitutionally aligned," or any equivalent
        phrase. Honest naming is required.

  (3.6) AMENDMENT BINDING
        The Constitutional Kernel itself may be amended ONLY by
        the original authority (KM-1176) or by a clearly-signed
        successor authority that publishes a public seal in the
        same chain (Anchor 1176-INFINITY-RHO and successor seals).
        Local Derivative Works may layer additional invariants on
        top of K1–K4 but may not weaken them.

